---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/layout/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/layout/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="FIRE Strategies — How to Achieve Financial Independence"
  description="Learn the most effective FIRE strategies to achieve financial independence. From aggressive saving to investment approaches, discover what works for you."
  canonical="https://truefinancetools.com/learn/fire-strategies"
>
  <Header />

  <main>
    <section class="border-b border-hairline bg-canvas py-16 sm:py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6">
        <p class="mb-4 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-mute">Learn</p>
        <h1 class="mb-4 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink sm:text-4xl" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
          FIRE Strategies
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-body">Different approaches to achieve financial independence and early retirement.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <article class="bg-canvas py-12 sm:py-16">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6">
        <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none space-y-8 text-body">
          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">The Savings Rate Strategy</h2>
            <p>Your <strong>savings rate</strong> is the single most important factor in your FIRE journey. Here's why:</p>
            <p>If you save 10% of your income, it takes about 51 years to retire. Save 50%, and it drops to about 17 years. Save 70%, and you can retire in about 8.5 years.</p>
            <div class="overflow-x-auto">
              <table class="w-full text-left text-sm">
                <thead>
                  <tr class="border-b border-hairline">
                    <th class="pb-2 pr-4 text-xs font-medium text-mute">Savings Rate</th>
                    <th class="pb-2 text-xs font-medium text-mute">Years to Retirement</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="font-mono text-xs tabular-nums">
                  <tr class="border-b border-hairline/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4">10%</td><td class="py-2">51 years</td></tr>
                  <tr class="border-b border-hairline/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4">25%</td><td class="py-2">32 years</td></tr>
                  <tr class="border-b border-hairline/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4">50%</td><td class="py-2">17 years</td></tr>
                  <tr class="border-b border-hairline/50"><td class="py-2 pr-4">75%</td><td class="py-2">7 years</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4">80%</td><td class="py-2">5.5 years</td></tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">The Barista FIRE Strategy</h2>
            <p>Barista FIRE is a hybrid approach where you save enough to cover most expenses, then work a part-time job for benefits and extra income. This reduces the amount you need to save while still achieving semi-retirement.</p>
            <p>Popular with those who enjoy some work but want freedom from the 9-5 grind.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">The House Hacking Strategy</h2>
            <p>House hacking involves buying a multi-unit property, living in one unit, and renting out the others. The rental income can cover your mortgage, dramatically reducing your housing costs — often your largest expense.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">The Geographic Arbitrage Strategy</h2>
            <p>Move to a location with a lower cost of living while maintaining your income (or working remotely). Your FIRE number becomes much smaller when your annual expenses drop.</p>
            <p>Popular destinations include Portugal, Mexico, Thailand, and Vietnam.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold text-ink">Investment Strategies</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
                <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Index Fund Investing</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-body">Invest in low-cost index funds like VTSAX or VTI. Simple, diversified, and historically returns 7-10% annually.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
                <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Real Estate Investing</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-body">Rental properties can provide passive income and appreciation. Requires more active management but can accelerate FIRE.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
                <h3 class="mb-1 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Dividend Investing</h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-body">Focus on dividend-paying stocks for regular income. More conservative approach with steady cash flow.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="rounded-lg bg-canvas-soft-2 p-6">
            <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Calculate Your FIRE Number</h2>
            <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-body">See which strategy works best for your situation with our free calculator.</p>
            <a
              href="/fire-calculator"
              class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full bg-ink px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-white transition-opacity hover:opacity-90"
            >
              Open Calculator
              <svg class="h-4 w-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6" />
              </svg>
            </a>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
